{"heading":[["1–5","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/93.1-5"],", All who are faithful will see the Lord; ",["6–18","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/93.6-18"],", John bore record that the Son of God went from grace to grace until He received a fulness of the glory of the Father; ",["19–20","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/93.19-20"],", Faithful men, going from grace to grace, will also receive of His fulness; ",["21–22","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/93.21-22"],", Those who are begotten through Christ are the Church of the Firstborn; ",["23–28","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/93.23-28"],", Christ received a fulness of all truth, and man by obedience may do likewise; ",["29–32","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/93.29-32"],", Man was in the beginning with God; ",["33–35","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/93.33-35"],", The elements are eternal, and man may receive a fulness of joy in the Resurrection; ",["36–37","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/93.36-37"],", The glory of God is intelligence; ",["38–40","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/93.38-40"],", Children are innocent before God because of the redemption of Christ; ",["41–53","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/93.41-53"],", The leading brethren are commanded to set their families in order."],"number":93,"verseCount":53,"verses":[[1,["Verily, thus saith the Lord: It shall come to pass that every soul who ",["forsaketh",["study-note-ref","a",[["Rom. 12:1 (1–3)","nt/rom/12.1"],"."]]]," his ",["sins",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Worthiness","tg/worthiness"],"."]]]," and cometh unto me, and ",["calleth",["study-note-ref","c",[["Joel 2:32","ot/joel/2.32"],"."]]]," on my name, and ",["obeyeth",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Obedience","tg/obedience"],"."]]]," my voice, and keepeth my commandments, shall ",["see",["study-note-ref","e",[["Lev. 9:4","ot/lev/9.4"],"; ",["John 14:23 (18, 21–23)","nt/john/14.23"],"; ",["D&C 38:8","dc-testament/dc/38.8"],"; ",["67:10 (10–12)","dc-testament/dc/67.10"],"; ",["88:68","dc-testament/dc/88.68"